items.html: Find out how much you’ll pay for a prescription drug with the Check Drug Cost & Coverage tool!
This tool from our pharmacy partner, CVS Caremark, will show you:
• If your Devoted Health plan covers the drug
• What you can expect to pay based on your specific plan, coverage stage, pharmacy, and more
How do I check the cost of my prescription?
To get started, log in at CVS Caremark. If you don’t have a CVS Caremark account yet, you’ll need to register. Make sure you have your Devoted Health member ID card handy.
Sign in to CVS Caremark
Once you’re signed in with CVS Caremark:
• Go to Plan & Benefits and select Check Drug Cost & Coverage.
• Compare prices for brand names, generics, and similar drugs that your plan covers. (Don’t see a price? That means your plan doesn’t cover it.)
• Compare costs for different pharmacies in your plan’s network, including in-person and mail order options.
Watch this video to learn more about using the Check Drug Cost & Coverage tool:
Devoted Health Guides are here 8am to 8pm, 7 days a week.
Or call us at 1-800-DEVOTED (338–6833) TTY 711
